				\begin{document}$$X^{ia}_M$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M10"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ia</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq4.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> correspond to the number of methylated reads from the reference <italic>r</italic> allele, and the alternative <italic>a</italic> allele. In practice, it makes no difference which allele is the reference or the alternative. <inline-formula id="IEq5"><alternatives><tex-math id="M11">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
