				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} L(\text{ASM}_{\text{tuple}}) = \sqrt{\left| {\text{ASM}_{\text{tuple}}}\right| } \end{aligned}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M254" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>tuple</mml:mtext></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msqrt><mml:mfenced close="|" open="|"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>tuple</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:mfenced></mml:msqrt></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_Equ6.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      </sec>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec27">
      <title>allelicmeth</title>
      <p id="Par55"><bold>allelicmeth</bold> (<bold>MethPipe</bold> version 3.4.3) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR34">34</xref>] is a tool that also detects ASM for a given sample directly from BS-seq reads. The tool is part of the <bold>MethPipe</bold> pipeline [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR66">66</xref>], which does not use standard bam files. We used commands from the pipeline to transform our <bold>bismark</bold> bam files from the CRC dataset into <italic>mr</italic> files, the input to <bold>allelicmeth</bold>. The output is a bed file with <italic>p</italic> values for each pair of CpG sites, reflecting the degree of allele specificity.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec28">
      <title>amrfinder</title>
      <p id="Par56"><bold>amrfinder</bold> (<bold>MethPipe</bold> version 3.4.3) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR34">34</xref>] also detects ASM from the BS-seq reads, however it generates regional scores. As with <bold>allelicmeth</bold>, we transformed <bold>bismark</bold> bam files from the CRC dataset into <italic>mr</italic> files, then ran <italic>methstates</italic> to generate <italic>epiread</italic> files, and used these to run <bold>amrfinder</bold> with default parameters. The output is a bed file with <italic>p</italic> values for each genomic region with consistent ASM.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec29">
      <title>Score evaluation</title>
      <p id="Par57">We converted the <inline-formula id="IEq122"><alternatives><tex-math id="M255">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{snp}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M256"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>snp</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq122.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> into a tuple-<inline-formula id="IEq123"><alternatives><tex-math id="M257">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{snp}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M258"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>snp</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq123.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> as <inline-formula id="IEq124"><alternatives><tex-math id="M259">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\left|\frac{X^{i1r}_M + X^{i2r}_M}{X^{i1r} + X^{i2r}} - \frac{X^{i1a}_M + X^{i2a}_M}{X^{i1a} + X^{i2a}}\right|$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M260"><mml:mfenced close="|" open="|"><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>r</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mi>r</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>r</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mi>r</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq124.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where 1 and 2 are the the first and second CpG site in a tuple <italic>i</italic>. We treated this converted score as true allele-specific methylation to test our scores at two thresholds: <inline-formula id="IEq125"><alternatives><tex-math id="M261">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\ge$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M262"><mml:mo>≥</mml:mo></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq125.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> 0.5 and <inline-formula id="IEq126"><alternatives><tex-math id="M263">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\ge$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M264"><mml:mo>≥</mml:mo></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq126.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> 0.8.</p>
      <p id="Par58">We transformed the <italic>p</italic> values generated by <bold>allelicmeth</bold> and <bold>amrfinder</bold> with a negative log base 10. We assigned the same transformed <italic>p</italic> values to all CpG tuples included in a single <bold>amrfinder</bold> region.</p>
      <p id="Par59">We also compared to a score based on whether the proportion of methylated reads to total number of reads deviates from 0.5, but transformed so a value of 0.5 is indicative of high ASM, and 1 or 0 is the lowest ASM. The score is <inline-formula id="IEq127"><alternatives><tex-math id="M265">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1-2(\left| \text{methylation} - 0.5 \right| )$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M266"><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mfenced close="|" open="|"><mml:mtext>methylation</mml:mtext><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>0.5</mml:mn></mml:mfenced><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq127.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>.</p>
      <p id="Par60">We used these four metrics to build ROC curves at different read coverages (5–9, 10–49 and <inline-formula id="IEq128"><alternatives><tex-math id="M267">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\ge$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M268"><mml:mo>≥</mml:mo></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq128.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> 50) and at different thresholds of <inline-formula id="IEq129"><alternatives><tex-math id="M269">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{snp}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M270"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>snp</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq129.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, for a single normal mucosa sample in the CRC dataset.</p>
      <p id="Par61">As an additional validation, we used the Blood dataset to obtain the <inline-formula id="IEq130"><alternatives><tex-math id="M271">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{tuple}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M272"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>tuple</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq130.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> scores from the promoters of known imprinted genes reported in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR11">11</xref>]. Only gene symbols that were traceable with <bold>biomaRt</bold> [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR67">67</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR68">68</xref>] were included, and genes labelled to be imprinted in placenta were removed, as indicated in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR69">69</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR70">70</xref>].</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec30">
      <title>t-statistic calculation</title>
      <p id="Par62">From the <bold>limma</bold> R package [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR39">39</xref>], we use <bold>lmFit</bold> to fit a linear model for each CpG position, and <bold>eBayes</bold> to calculate a moderated t-statistic on the transformed <inline-formula id="IEq131"><alternatives><tex-math id="M273">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{tuple}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M274"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>tuple</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq131.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> score, or on the <inline-formula id="IEq132"><alternatives><tex-math id="M275">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{ASM}_{\text{snp}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M276"><mml:msub><mml:mtext>ASM</mml:mtext><mml:mtext>snp</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq132.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> score. For the former, we set the median of two CpGs in a tuple as the CpG position of that tuple. Transformed ASM scores across samples are given as input to <bold>lmFit</bold>, as well as a design matrix that specifies the conditions of the samples of interest. As specified in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR39">39</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR71">71</xref>], a CpG site-wise or tuple-wise linear model is defined as<disp-formula id="Equ7"><label>7</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M277">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} E(y_i) = X\beta _i \end{aligned}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M278" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>y</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_Equ7.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where for each CpG site or tuple <italic>i</italic>, we have a vector of ASM scores <inline-formula id="IEq133"><alternatives><tex-math id="M279">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$y_i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M280"><mml:msub><mml:mi>y</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq133.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and a design matrix <italic>X</italic> that relates these values to some coefficients of interest <inline-formula id="IEq134"><alternatives><tex-math id="M281">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\beta _i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M282"><mml:msub><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq134.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>.</p>
      <p id="Par63">In the end, we test for a specific contrast that <inline-formula id="IEq135"><alternatives><tex-math id="M283">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Ho: C_{\beta _{ij}} = 0$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M284"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mi>o</mml:mi><mml:mo>:</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>C</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq135.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec31">
      <title>Smoothing</title>
      <p id="Par64">We group the positions into genomic clusters using the <bold>clusterMaker</bold> function from the <bold>bumphunter</bold> R package [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR40">40</xref>]. Then, we use the <bold>loessByCluster</bold> function to perform loess within each cluster, and obtain <inline-formula id="IEq136"><alternatives><tex-math id="M285">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\tilde{\beta }}_{ij}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M286"><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2020_346_Article_IEq136.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, our smoothed estimate.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec32">
      <title>FDR control evaluation</title>
      <p id="Par65">We selected 6 samples of normal tissue from the CRC dataset and calculated their <inline-formula id="IEq137"><alternatives><tex-math id="M287">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
