      <p id="Par66">We generated 50 of these simulations, and for each of them, ran DAMEfinder with the cluster-wise correction, and the permutation correction (Additional file <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref>: Figure S10 for distributions of null and observed areas) with three different <italic>K</italic> thresholds: 0.2, 0.5, 0.8. We used the <bold>iCOBRA</bold> R package (version 1.12.1) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR72">72</xref>] to calculate TPR and FDR at different adjusted <italic>p</italic> value thresholds: 0.01, 0.05, 0.1.</p>
